---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
const schema = [
  {
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Free APIs Guide",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "SiliconBased Editorial"
    }
  },
  {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are Unsplash API images free to use?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, the Unsplash API provides access to royalty-free images, but you must adhere to their attribution guidelines and rate limits."
        }
      },

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I get random placeholder images?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You can use Lorem Picsum, a free service that returns random placeholder images of any specified size via a simple URL."
        }
      },

      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Cloudinary free?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Cloudinary offers a generous free tier (25 monthly credits) which is often enough for personal projects requiring image hosting and transformation."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

export const meta = {
  title: "Best Free Image & Media APIs",
  description: "Unsplash, Pexels, Lorem Picsum, Cloudinary. Explore best free image & media apis with our free interactive tool and guide.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---
<SiteLayout site="siliconbased" title="Best Free Image & Media APIs" description="Unsplash, Pexels, Lorem Picsum, Cloudinary. Explore best free image & media apis with our free interactive tool and guide." canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/free-image-apis" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Best Free Image & Media APIs</h1>
      <p>Unsplash, Pexels, Lorem Picsum, Cloudinary.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="article-body">

    <h2>Enhancing UI with Media APIs</h2>
    <p>Images are vital for user engagement. Whether you need placeholder images for a mockup or a dynamic library of high-quality stock photos, these free image APIs provide the necessary resources.</p>

    <h3>1. Unsplash API</h3>
    <p>Unsplash boasts a massive library of high-resolution, royalty-free images contributed by a global community of photographers. Their API allows you to integrate this library directly into your applications.</p>
    <p>You can search for images by keyword, retrieve random images, or fetch images from specific user collections.</p>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>Usage Guidelines:</h4>
      <p>Unsplash requires developers to follow specific attribution guidelines, such as linking back to the photographer's profile and the Unsplash homepage.</p>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> Demo applications are limited to 50 requests per hour. Once your application is reviewed and approved for production, this limit is raised.</p>

    <h3>2. Pexels API</h3>
    <p>Pexels is a strong alternative to Unsplash, providing both high-quality photos and stock videos. Their API is straightforward and well-documented.</p>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> The Pexels API is entirely free, with a generous rate limit of 200 requests per hour and 20,000 requests per month.</p>

    <h3>3. Lorem Picsum</h3>
    <p>Often referred to as the "Lorem Ipsum for photos," Lorem Picsum provides a simple, URL-based API for generating placeholder images. It is incredibly useful during the frontend development phase.</p>
    <p>Example usage: <code>https://picsum.photos/200/300</code> will return a random image that is 200px wide and 300px high.</p>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> Completely free, no API key required.</p>

    <h3>4. Cloudinary</h3>
    <p>Cloudinary is fundamentally different from the others; it is an image and video management platform. It allows you to upload media and dynamically transform it via URL parameters (e.g., resizing, cropping, applying filters, changing formats to WebP).</p>
    <p><strong>Free Tier Details:</strong> The free tier provides 25 monthly credits. One credit equals 1,000 transformations, 1GB of storage, or 1GB of bandwidth. This is typically sufficient for personal blogs and small portfolios.</p>

    <p><em>Return to the <a href="/best-free-apis-2026">Best Free APIs 2026</a> overview.</em></p>
    <h2>Related Guides</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/free-ai-apis">Free AI APIs</a></li>
      <li><a href="/free-weather-apis">Free Weather APIs</a></li>
    </ul>


    </div>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
    console.log("Loaded Best Free Image & Media APIs");
  </script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .article-body h2 { color: var(--accent-color); font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .article-body p { line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .article-body ul { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .article-body a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
    .article-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .article-body pre { background: #0c1218; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; overflow-x: auto; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .article-body code { font-family: monospace; color: #e0e8f0; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
